Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

While the water boils, peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve, peel, and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and diced) into small pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large, wide-bottomed #ovenproof pan{} on medium heat.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an ovenproof dish before baking.

Once the oil is hot, add the onion to the #pan{} and stir-fry until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the @risotto rice{175%grams}, @diced British chicken breast{1%pack}, garlic and @tomato puree{30%grams} and stir and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @water{500%milliliter} for the risotto and @vegetable stock paste{20%grams}. Bring back up to the boil, then pop a #lid{} on the pan (or cover with #foil{}) and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water has been absorbed, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the risotto bakes, zest and cut the @lemon{1} into wedges. Trim the @Brussels sprouts{200%grams} and halve through the root.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the sprouts to the frying pan and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Stir-fry until starting to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once browned, add a splash of @water{} to the sprouts and immediately cover with a lid or some foil. Allow to cook until the sprouts are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, mix together the lemon zest, @olive oil{2%tbsp} and @sugar{1/2%tsp} for the dressing. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

When the sprouts have finished cooking, remove from the heat and stir in the @honey{15%grams}.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Transfer them to the #bowl{} with the dressing and set aside for later.

When the risotto is cooked, remove it from the oven and stir the @baby spinach{40%grams} to the dish a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Next, stir through the @vegan 'Nduja{1/2%sachet}, @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%grams}, a squeeze of lemon juice and the @butter{20%grams}. Taste and season with @salt{}, @pepper{} or more lemon juice if needed.

> TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the risotto if needed.

Share your chicken and veggie 'Nduja risotto between your #serving plates{}.

Top with your sticky sprouts.

Serve the lemon wedges on the side.

Enjoy!